==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Canister
<hw>Can"is*ter</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧n"⟦icr⟧s*t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>canistrum</ets> a basket woven from reeds Gr. <?/, fr.
<grk>ka`nh</grk>, <grk>ka`nna</grk> reed; cf. F. <ets>canistre</ets>.
See <er>Cane</er>, and <er>Canaster</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
small basket of rushes, reeds, or willow twigs, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small box or case for holding tea, coffee,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A kind of case shot for cannon, in
which a number of lead or iron balls in layers are inclosed in a case
fitting the gun; -- called also <altname>canister
shot</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Canker</ent>⟦br⟧
